{"title_page": "Gokuladasi", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2017}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Gokuladasi\n| image          = Gokuladasi 1948 poster.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Theatrical poster\n| director       = [[Krishnaswami Subrahmanyam|K. Subrahmanyam]]\n| producer       = [[Krishnaswami Subrahmanyam|K. Subrahmanyam]]\n| writer         = Elangovan\n| screenplay     = [[Krishnaswami Subrahmanyam|K. Subrahmanyam]]\n| story          = Elangovan\n| based on       = \n| starring       = [[Honnappa Bhagavathar|C. Honnappa Bhagavathar]]<br/>[[M. V. Rajamma]]<br/>[[T. R. Ramachandran]]<br/>N. Krishnamurthi<br/>[[Lalitha (actress)|Lalitha]]<br/>[[Padmini (actress)|Padmini]]\n| narrator       = \n| music          = [[S. V. Venkatraman]]<ref name=anandan>{{cite book|url=http://www.lakshmansruthi.com/cineprofiles/1948-cinedetails10.asp|title=Sadhanaigal Padaitha Thamizh Thiraipada Varalaru|trans-title=History of Landmark Tamil Films|publisher=Sivakami Publishers|author=Film News Anandan|authorlink=Film News Anandan|date=23 October 2004|location=Chennai|language=Tamil|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170529080102/http://www.lakshmansruthi.com/cineprofiles/1948-cinedetails10.asp|archivedate=29 May 2017|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n| cinematography = P. L. Rai\n| editing        = R. Rajagopal\n| studio         = Madras United Artistes Corporation\n| distributor    = Madras United Artistes Corporation\n| released       = {{film date|df=yes|1948|11|31|India}}<ref name=anandan/>\n| runtime        = \n| country        = [[India]]\n| language       = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n'''''Gokuladasi''''' ({{Trans|Gokulam's Devotee}}) is a [[List of Tamil films of 1948|1948]] Indian [[Tamil language]] film directed and produced by [[Krishnaswami Subrahmanyam]]. The film featured [[Honnappa Bhagavathar|C. Honnappa Bhagavathar]] and [[M. V. Rajamma]] in the lead roles with [[T. R. Ramachandran]], N. Krishnamurthi, [[Lalitha (actress)|Lalitha]] and [[Padmini (actress)|Padmini]] playing supporting roles.<ref name=BFTPhindu>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-cinemaplus/gokuladasi-1949/article13385074.ece|title=Gokuladasi 1949|work=[[The Hindu]]|date=29 January 2012|accessdate=29 May 2017|last=Guy|first=Randor|authorlink=Randor Guy|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170529080712/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-cinemaplus/gokuladasi-1949/article13385074.ece|archivedate=29 May 2017|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nKamaroopan (Honnappa Bhagavathar) is a lustful king who faces the curse of Goddess [[Parvati]] and is reborn as a common jeweller in the town of Gokulam. The jeweller happens to set his eyes on a ''[[Devadasi]]'' named Anuradha (Rajamma) and tries to woo her. Anuradha on the other hand, was a singer-dancer in her previous birth and a devotee of Parvati. She was cursed by sage [[Narada]] (Honnappa Bhagavathar) for displeasing him and is reborn as Anuradha. The jeweller keeps trying to seduce Anuradha not realising the actions he had committed in his previous birth. To settle the matter, [[Krishna]] (Padmini) rids both the jeweller and the ''Devadasi'' of their curses.<ref name=BFTPhindu />\n\n==Cast==\nAdapted from [[Film News Anandan]] and ''[[The Hindu]]''.<ref name=anandan/><ref name=BFTPhindu />\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n*[[Honnappa Bhagavathar|C. Honnappa Bhagavathar]] as [[Narada]]/Kamaroopan/a jeweller\n*[[M. V. Rajamma]] as a singer-dancer/Anuradha\n*[[T. R. Ramachandran]]\n*N. Krishnamurthi\n*[[Lalitha (actress)|Lalitha]]\n*[[Padmini (actress)|Padmini]] as [[Krishna]]\n*Sowdhamini\n*R. M. Somasundaram\n*N. Thiruvengadam\n*K. S. Angamuthu\n*S. Sarojini\n*Baby Sathyavathi\n\n;Dance\n*Lalitha\n*Padmini\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Production==\n[[Krishnaswami Subrahmanyam]] directed and produced the film under his own banner, the Madras United Artistes Corporation.<ref name=anandan/> The story and dialogues were written by Ilangovan while Subrahmanyam himself handled the screenplay.<ref name=anandan/><ref name=BFTPhindu /> [[Principal photography]] for the film took place at Neptune Studios.<ref name=BFTPhindu /> One of the film's associate directors was L. Krishnan, who later went on to become a prominent filmmaker in [[Cinema of Malaysia|Malaysian cinema]] and earned the [[Datuk]] honorific.<ref name=BFTPhindu />\n\n==Soundtrack==\n[[S. V. Venkatraman]] was in charge of the music and score for ''Gokuladasi'' while the songs' lyrics were written by [[Papanasam Sivan]] and Rajagopal Iyer.<ref name=BFTPhindu />\n\n==Reception==\nFilm historian [[Randor Guy]] notes that ''Gokuladasi'' is \"remembered for the pleasing music, song and dance numbers by the Travancore Sisters and impressive performances by Rajamma, Honnappa Bhagavathar and T. R. Ramachandran.\"<ref name=BFTPhindu /> The film did not perform well at the box office.<ref name=BFTPhindu />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1948 films]]\n[[Category:Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian drama films]]\n[[Category:Indian black-and-white films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Films about reincarnation]]\n[[Category:1940s drama films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2017}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Gokuladasi\n| image          = Gokuladasi 1948 poster.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Theatrical poster\n| director       = [[Krishnaswami Subrahmanyam|K. Subrahmanyam]]\n| producer       = [[Krishnaswami Subrahmanyam|K. Subrahmanyam]]\n| writer         = Elangovan\n| screenplay     = [[Krishnaswami Subrahmanyam|K. Subrahmanyam]]\n| story          = Elangovan\n| based on       = \n| starring       = [[Honnappa Bhagavathar|C. Honnappa Bhagavathar]]<br/>[[M. V. Rajamma]]<br/>[[T. R. Ramachandran]]<br/>N. Krishnamurthi<br/>[[Lalitha (actress)|Lalitha]]<br/>[[Padmini (actress)|Padmini]]\n| narrator       = \n| music          = [[S. V. Venkatraman]]<ref name=anandan>{{cite book|url=http://www.lakshmansruthi.com/cineprofiles/1948-cinedetails10.asp|title=Sadhanaigal Padaitha Thamizh Thiraipada Varalaru|trans-title=History of Landmark Tamil Films|publisher=Sivakami Publishers|author=Film News Anandan|authorlink=Film News Anandan|date=23 October 2004|location=Chennai|language=Tamil|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170529080102/http://www.lakshmansruthi.com/cineprofiles/1948-cinedetails10.asp|archivedate=29 May 2017|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n| cinematography = P. L. Rai\n| editing        = R. Rajagopal\n| studio         = Madras United Artistes Corporation\n| distributor    = Madras United Artistes Corporation\n| released       = {{film date|df=yes|1948|11|31|India}}<ref name=anandan/>\n| runtime        = \n| country        = [[India]]\n| language       = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n'''''Gokuladasi''''' (''Gokulam's Devotee'') is a [[List of Tamil films of 1948|1948]] Indian [[Tamil language]] film directed and produced by [[Krishnaswami Subrahmanyam]]. The film featured [[Honnappa Bhagavathar|C. Honnappa Bhagavathar]] and [[M. V. Rajamma]] in the lead roles with [[T. R. Ramachandran]], N. Krishnamurthi, [[Lalitha (actress)|Lalitha]] and [[Padmini (actress)|Padmini]] playing supporting roles.<ref name=BFTPhindu>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-cinemaplus/gokuladasi-1949/article13385074.ece|title=Gokuladasi 1949|work=[[The Hindu]]|date=29 January 2012|accessdate=29 May 2017|last=Guy|first=Randor|authorlink=Randor Guy|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170529080712/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-cinemaplus/gokuladasi-1949/article13385074.ece|archivedate=29 May 2017|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nKamaroopan (Honnappa Bhagavathar) is a lustful king who faces the curse of Goddess [[Parvati]] and is reborn as a common jeweller in the town of Gokulam. The jeweller happens to set his eyes on a ''[[Devadasi]]'' named Anuradha (Rajamma) and tries to woo her. Anuradha on the other hand, was a singer-dancer in her previous birth and a devotee of Parvati. She was cursed by sage [[Narada]] (Honnappa Bhagavathar) for displeasing him and is reborn as Anuradha. The jeweller keeps trying to seduce Anuradha not realising the actions he had committed in his previous birth. To settle the matter, [[Krishna]] (Padmini) rids both the jeweller and the ''Devadasi'' of their curses.<ref name=BFTPhindu />\n\n==Cast==\nAdapted from [[Film News Anandan]] and ''[[The Hindu]]''.<ref name=anandan/><ref name=BFTPhindu />\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n*[[Honnappa Bhagavathar|C. Honnappa Bhagavathar]] as [[Narada]]/Kamaroopan/a jeweller\n*[[M. V. Rajamma]] as a singer-dancer/Anuradha\n*[[T. R. Ramachandran]]\n*N. Krishnamurthi\n*[[Lalitha (actress)|Lalitha]]\n*[[Padmini (actress)|Padmini]] as [[Krishna]]\n*Sowdhamini\n*R. M. Somasundaram\n*N. Thiruvengadam\n*K. S. Angamuthu\n*S. Sarojini\n*Baby Sathyavathi\n\n;Dance\n*Lalitha\n*Padmini\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Production==\n[[Krishnaswami Subrahmanyam]] directed and produced the film under his own banner, the Madras United Artistes Corporation.<ref name=anandan/> The story and dialogues were written by Ilangovan while Subrahmanyam himself handled the screenplay.<ref name=anandan/><ref name=BFTPhindu /> [[Principal photography]] for the film took place at Neptune Studios.<ref name=BFTPhindu /> One of the film's associate directors was L. Krishnan, who later went on to become a prominent filmmaker in [[Cinema of Malaysia|Malaysian cinema]] and earned the [[Datuk]] honorific.<ref name=BFTPhindu />\n\n==Soundtrack==\n[[S. V. Venkatraman]] was in charge of the music and score for ''Gokuladasi'' while the songs' lyrics were written by [[Papanasam Sivan]] and Rajagopal Iyer.<ref name=BFTPhindu />\n\n==Reception==\nFilm historian [[Randor Guy]] notes that ''Gokuladasi'' is \"remembered for the pleasing music, song and dance numbers by the Travancore Sisters and impressive performances by Rajamma, Honnappa Bhagavathar and T. R. Ramachandran.\"<ref name=BFTPhindu /> The film did not perform well at the box office.<ref name=BFTPhindu />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1948 films]]\n[[Category:Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian drama films]]\n[[Category:Indian black-and-white films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Films about reincarnation]]\n[[Category:1940s drama films]]\n", "name_user": "Titodutta", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eGokuladasi:fmt // Edit via Wikiplus", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gokuladasi"}
